== [http://scummvm.sourceforge.net ScummVM] ==
[[File:Scummvm_screenshot1.png|thumb|right|200px|[http://scummvm.sourceforge.net/screenshots media]]]

ScummVM is a reimplementation of the SCUMM game engine used in Lucasarts point-and-click adventures (such as Monkey Island 1-3, Day of the Tentacle, Sam & Max, ...), but also supports Sierra's AGI and SCI games (such as King's Quest 1-6, Space Quest 1-5, ...), {{Package|games-rpg/bass}}, {{Package|games-rpg/queen}}, {{Package|games-rpg/drascula}} and [http://scummvm.sourceforge.net/compatibility many more]. Note that it always requires the original game files. Portage also provides {{Package|games-engines/scummvm-tools}} which is a collection of utilities to extract data files from games, convert audio files and make video sequences usable under ScummVM.

